4 A BILL FOR AN ACT ENTITLED: “AN ACT REVISING ELECTOR REGISTRATION LAWS; REQUIRING THE
5 SECRETARY OF STATE TO DETERMINE THE UNITED STATES CITIZENSHIP STATUS OF REGISTERED
6 ELECTORS; REQUIRING THE SECRETARY OF STATE TO ALERT ELECTORS WHO HAVE AN
7 UNDETERMINED CITIZENSHIP OF THEIR STATUS AND PROVIDE THE ELECTORS WITH A MEANS FOR
8 DEMONSTRATING UNITED STATES CITIZENSHIP; REQUIRING THE SECRETARY OF STATE TO
9 REMOVE FROM THE LIST OF ELECTORS PERSONS DETERMINED TO HAVE NON-UNITED STATES
10 CITIZENSHIP STATUS; REQUIRING THE SECRETARY OF STATE TO ESTABLISH PROCEDURES TO
11 DETERMINE THE CITIZENSHIP STATUS OF NEW APPLICANTS; REQUIRING DOCUMENTARY PROOF
12 OF CITIZENSHIP BY NEW APPLICANTS AND PROVIDING FOR THE REMOVAL OF ELECTORS WITH
13 UNDETERMINED CITIZENSHIP STATUS WHO DO NOT SUBSEQUENTLY DEMONSTRATE UNITED
14 STATES CITIZENSHIP STATUS IN THE EVENT THAT THE FEDERAL GOVERNMENT ALLOWS OR
15 REQUIRES STATES TO DETERMINE CITIZENSHIP STATUS OF ELECTORS OR NEW APPLICANTS;
16 PROVIDING RULEMAKING AUTHORITY; AMENDING SECTIONS 13-2-108, 13-2-109, 13-2-110, 13-2-402,
17 AND 61-14-301, MCA; AND PROVIDING EFFECTIVE DATES.”
18
19 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF MONTANA:
20
21 Section 1. Section 13-2-108, MCA, is amended to read:
22 "13-2-108. Rulemaking for statewide voter registration list. (1) The secretary of state shall adopt
23 rules to implement the provisions of 42 U.S.C. 15483 and this chapter.
24 (2) The rules must include but are not limited to:
25 (a) (i) a list of maintenance procedures, including new data entry, updates, registration transfers,
26 and other procedures for keeping information current and accurate and for determining one of the following
27 three citizenship statuses for registered electors:
28 (A) United States citizenship;
