1 (B) undetermined citizenship; and
2 (C) non-United States citizenship; and
3 (ii) procedures for:
4 (A) alerting an elector with undetermined citizenship status of their status and providing a means
5 for that elector to demonstrate United States citizenship status; and
6 (B) removing from the list of electors a person determined to have non-United States citizenship
7 status;
8 (b) proper maintenance and use of active and inactive lists;
9 (c) proper maintenance and use of lists for legally registered electors and provisionally registered
10 electors;
11 (d) technical security of the statewide voter registration system;
12 (e) information security with respect to keeping from general public distribution driver's license
13 numbers, whole or partial social security numbers, and address information protected from general disclosure
14 pursuant to 13-2-115; and
15 (f) quality control measures for the system and system users.
16 (3) The rules adopted by the secretary of state must reflect that an elector who was properly
17 registered prior to January 1, 2003, is considered a legally registered elector."
18
19 Section 2. Section 13-2-109, MCA, is amended to read:
20 "13-2-109. Rulemaking on sufficiency and verification of voter registration information. (1) The
21 secretary of state shall adopt rules:
22 (a) to implement the provisions of 13-2-110 and this section concerning how election
23 administrators determine whether the information provided by an elector on an application for voter registration
24 is:
25 (i) sufficient to be accepted and processed; or
26 (ii) insufficient to be accepted and processed;
27 (b) establishing procedures for verifying the accuracy of voter registration information;
28 (c) establishing standards for determining whether an elector may be legally registered or
