7 Section 3. Section 13-2-110, MCA, is amended to read:
8 "13-2-110. Application for voter registration -- sufficiency and verification of information --
9 identifiers assigned for voting purposes -- rulemaking. (1) An individual may apply for voter registration in
10 person or by mail, postage paid, by completing and signing the standard application form for voter registration
11 provided for in 13-1-210 and providing the application to the election administrator in the county in which the
12 elector resides.
13 (2) Each application for voter registration must be accepted and processed as provided in rules
14 adopted under 13-2-109.
15 (3) The applicant shall provide documentary proof of United States citizenship in a manner
16 prescribed by the secretary of state through rulemaking.
17 (4) Except as provided in subsection (5), an applicant for voter registration shall provide the
18 applicant's:
19 (a) Montana driver's license number;
20 (b) Montana state identification card number issued pursuant to 61-12-501; or
21 (c) the last four digits of the applicant's social security number.
22 (5) (a) If an applicant is unable to provide information in accordance with subsection (3) (4), the
23 applicant shall provide as an alternative form of identification:
24 (i) a military identification card, a tribal photo identification card, a United States passport, or a
25 Montana concealed carry permit; or
26 (ii) (A) any other form of photo identification, including but not limited to a school district or
27 postsecondary education photo identification with the individual's name; and
28 (B) a current utility bill, bank statement, paycheck, government check, or other government
