1 document that shows the individual's name and current address.
2 (b) The alternative form of identification must be:
3 (i) an original version presented to the election administrator if the applicant is applying in person;
4 or
5 (ii) a readable copy of any of the required documents, which must be enclosed with the
6 application, if the applicant is applying by mail.
7 (6) (a) If information provided on an application for voter registration is sufficient to be accepted
8 and processed and is verified pursuant to rules adopted under 13-2-109, the election administrator shall
9 register the elector as a legally registered elector.
10 (b) If information provided on an application for voter registration was sufficient to be accepted but
11 the applicant failed to provide the information required in subsection (3) or (4) (4) or (5) or if the information
12 provided was incorrect or insufficient to verify the individual's identity or eligibility to vote, the election
13 administrator shall register the applicant as a provisionally registered elector.
14 (7) Each applicant for voter registration must be notified of the elector's registration status pursuant
15 to rules adopted under 13-2-109.
16 (8) The secretary of state shall assign to each elector whose application was accepted a unique
17 identification number for voting purposes and shall establish a statewide uniform method to allow the secretary
18 of state and local election officials to distinguish legally registered electors from provisionally registered
19 electors.
20 (9) The provisions of this section may not be interpreted to conflict with voter registration
21 accomplished under 13-2-221, 13-21-221, and 61-5-107 and as provided for in federal law."
