1 submitted to the county under 50-15-409 or through a newspaper obituary;
2 (3) the elector is of unsound mind as established by a court;
3 (4) the incarceration of the elector in a penal institution for a felony conviction is legally
4 established;
5 (5) a certified copy of a court order directing the cancellation is filed with the election administrator;
6 (6) a notice is received from the secretary of state or from another county or state that the elector
7 has registered in another county or state;
8 (7) the elector:
9 (a) fails to respond to certain confirmation mailings;
10 (b) is placed on the inactive list; and
11 (c) then fails to vote in two consecutive federal general elections; or
12 (8) the elector has been informed by the secretary of state that the elector has an undetermined
13 United States citizenship status and fails to demonstrate United States citizenship in the manner prescribed by
14 the secretary of state through rulemaking; or
15 (9) the elector fails to meet any voter qualification that is listed in 13-1-111."
